<Author>gazzawaz
<Content>Clean, Central and Reasonable The reviews here seem to be very mixed but my personal experience of the Maas was very good.There were three of us sharing and when we reached our room, we all thought that it was a bit cramped. However it was also very clean. The next morning we all agreed that we had all slept very well; the beds are very comfortable!The bathroom was spotless and the shower was really strong - great for that really clean feeling. The Hotel Maas is located near Leidseplein. This is a lively area full of bars and restaurants and a great place to sit and watch the world go by.We were a short walk to the Museumplein with the Van Gogh and Rembrandt museums. In the other direction we were very close to Kalverstraat, one of the main shopping areas. Also we were close to Rembrandtplein etc.Some of my friends were staying at the top of Damrak and while they were close to some areas, they were fairly distant from the museums.The staff were very helpful and organised a taxi for us to the airport on our last day.Overall I would recommend the Maas if you are looking for a reasonable central place to stay in Amsterdam. If you are looking for luxury or a very romantic setting then i think this is not the place for you. 
