<Content>Hotel Maas-a wonderful experience We rented out 10 rooms for my daughter's wedding in May 2003. I wasn't sure what we were getting, but was very pleasantly surprised with Hotel Maas. The staff was unbelievably helpful with all of our requests...from arranging for her wedding dress to be steamed to shuffling our rooms around as people arrived!! They definitely went above and beyond the call of duty. The hotel location turned out to be perfect. The museums are right at your fingertips and the Damrack (and shopping) is an easy walk. (Everyone's first order of sightseeing was the Heineken Museum just down the street!!) The rooms are smaller but clean and ample. Those with the canal view (160 euros) have a very pretty view. The breakfast area was nice with a decent selection of food items. Night life was in full swing right next door at the American Hotel. All in all a good find. Any problems that might surface would be handled well with the professional staff. I have to add it was a treat to stay in an authentic Amsterdam canal house rather than the big American hotel. Why stay in one of those when you can experience a bit of authentic Europe?? 
