<Content>A hidden treasure A wonderful find! Typical steep Dutch steps to the lobby but worth the hike to a delightful stay. Superior staff, extremely accomodating to tourist requests. Hotel is not full of Americans but many thrifty (not stingy) Europeans. Small but bright rooms. Small converted bathrooms, most with shower but some with tubs, some even with Jaccuzzi. Less than $100/night. Ample Dutch breakfast included. Outstanding location on Leidesekade at Leidseplein, around the corner from the overpriced American Hotel. Really good transportation hub for taxis and trams. KLM shuttle drop is across the canal. Convenient walking for the Reiksmuseum, Van Gogh, Stedelijk, Concertbegouw, Boom Chicago, Anne Frank, Rembrandt Huis, Flower Market (and the hotel will provide a vase for your purchase), shopping on the Kalverstraat or P.C.Hooftstraat, everything. Excellent restaurants in the neighborhood. Casino a block away. Very busy area but not nearly as noisy as the Rembrand!tsplein.Would I stay there again? Absolutely!! 
